<inglise> Whereas: </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) Section 2 of Title II of Regulation (EC) No 2820/98 provides for the possibility of granting special incentive arrangements concerning labour rights. </inglise>
<eesti> 1) m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 2820/98 II jaotise 2. jaoga n&auml;hakse ette t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &otilde;iguste kaitset k&auml;sitleva stimuleeriva erikorra andmise v&otilde;imalus; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) On 11 February 1999, the Republic of Moldova submitted a request for taking advantage of this regime, giving the information and the commitment referred to in Article 11(1) of the aforementioned Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> 2) 11. veebruaril 1999. aastal esitas Moldova Vabariik taotluse k&otilde;nealuse korra kohaldamise kohta, edastades eespool nimetatud m&auml;&auml;ruse artikli 11 l&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud teabe ning v&otilde;ttes endale sellekohased kohustused; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) In accordance with Article 11(2), the Commission published a notice(3) announcing the request of the Republic of Moldova. </inglise>
<eesti> 3) vastavalt artikli 11 l&otilde;ikele 2 avaldas komisjon teadaande (3) Moldova Vabariigi taotluse kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) Certain interested parties made their comments known to the Commission. </inglise>
<eesti> 4) teatavad huvitatud pooled edastasid komisjonile oma t&auml;helepanekud; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) The request was examined in accordance with Article 12 of the aforementioned Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> 5) taotlus vaadati l&auml;bi eespool nimetatud m&auml;&auml;ruse artikli 12 kohaselt; </eesti>
<inglise> (6) The domestic legislation of the Republic of Moldova incorporates the substance of the standards laid down in ILO Conventions No 87, 98 and 138. </inglise>
<eesti> 6) Moldova Vabariigi siseriiklikud &otilde;igusaktid sisaldavad Rahvusvahelise T&ouml;&ouml;organisatsiooni (ILO) konventsioonide nr 87, 98 ja 138 norme; </eesti>
<inglise> (7) The examination carried out by the Commission showed that the Moldovan authorities have taken the necessary measures for the effective application and monitoring of these provisions. </inglise>
<eesti> 7) komisjoni teostatud l&auml;bivaatamine n&auml;itas, et Moldova ametiasutused on v&otilde;tnud k&otilde;nealuste s&auml;tete t&otilde;husaks kohaldamiseks ja kontrollimiseks vajalikud meetmed; </eesti>
<inglise> (8) The Republic of Moldova has committed itself to ensure the effective application and the control of the special arrangements as well as the administrative cooperation referred to in Article 14 of the aforementioned Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> 8) Moldova Vabariik kohustub tagama erikorra t&otilde;husa kohaldamise ja kontrolli ning eespool nimetatud m&auml;&auml;ruse artiklis 14 osutatud halduskoost&ouml;&ouml;; </eesti>
<inglise> (9) In the light of the comments received and of the findings of the examination, it is appropriate to approve the request. </inglise>
<eesti> 9) esitatud t&auml;helepanekuid ja l&auml;bivaatamise tulemusi silmas pidades on asjakohane taotlus rahuldada; </eesti>
<inglise> (10) The measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Committee referred to in Article 31 of the aforementioned Regulation, </inglise>
